  "description": "Survey of competing accounts of how knowledge relates to its recording — from Plato's separation of knowledge from writing through Briet's documentation theory, Polanyi's tacit dimension, Dewey's inquiry, archival diplomatics, and Haraway's situated knowledges. Maps the terrain between knowledge as a mental state and documentation as its constitutive practice.",
  "name": "Knowledge and Documentation: A Survey of Their Relationship",
